  "text": "2 Detect Outlier. To detect corrupted colors we can fit a global model between the extracted d i and a set of reference colors. These reference colors r i can be taken from the digital image of the marker or extracted from the first frames of the video in a pre-processing step. In order to keep the number of false positives low a conservative model should be fitted between the c i and r i . We chose the affine transformation model c i = A r i + t [CITATION_1] , which can be computed analytically and avoids over fitting to corrupted colors.",
